# agents/ directory
#
# Put one .md file per subagent your plugin uses. They load automatically and are
# namespaced by the plugin (e.g. <plugin>:<agent-name>).
#
# Required frontmatter:
#
#   ---
#   name: <agent-name>
#   description: >-
#     What this subagent does and when it is invoked.
#   tools: Read, Bash, Edit   # allowlist (optional; omit to inherit all)
#   model: sonnet             # sonnet | opus | haiku | fable
#   ---
#
# Note: plugin agents ignore an mcpServers/permissionMode/hooks block. To give an
# agent MCP tools, add the mcp__<server>__* names to its `tools` allowlist.
#
# Delete this file when you add your first real agent, or remove the whole folder if
# the plugin needs no subagents.
